    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"US Economy 2026\"\nsubtitle: \"A visual analysis — 2026 in the context of the past 25 years\"\n---\n\n\n\nThis site is an interactive drill-down analysis of the US economy in 2026 placed\nagainst the past 25 years (2001–2025). Use the top navigation to move between\nthe four panels, or click the links below.\n\n::: {.callout-note appearance=\"simple\"}\n**Prototype dataset.** Historical values are hand-entered from public sources\n(BEA, BLS, Federal Reserve, NBER, public market indices). Values for 2025 and\n2026 are *illustrative* — they are not forecasts. See the [About](about.qmd)\npage for regeneration instructions and how to swap in live FRED data.\n:::\n\n## 2026 Snapshot {#snapshot}\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div style=\"display:flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px; margin: 10px 0 20px;\">\n<div style=\"border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px;&#10;       background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);&#10;       min-width: 170px; flex: 1;\">\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.80rem; color:#6c757d; letter-spacing: .02em; text-transform: uppercase;\">Real GDP growth (YoY)</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 600; color: #2f9e44; line-height: 1.15; margin-top: 4px;\">+1.6%</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.82rem; color:#6c757d; margin-top: 2px;\">20ᵗʰ percentile vs 2001–2025</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px;&#10;       background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);&#10;       min-width: 170px; flex: 1;\">\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.80rem; color:#6c757d; letter-spacing: .02em; text-transform: uppercase;\">Unemployment rate</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 600; color: #2f9e44; line-height: 1.15; margin-top: 4px;\">4.5%</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.82rem; color:#6c757d; margin-top: 2px;\">28ᵗʰ percentile (lower = better)</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px;&#10;       background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);&#10;       min-width: 170px; flex: 1;\">\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.80rem; color:#6c757d; letter-spacing: .02em; text-transform: uppercase;\">CPI inflation (YoY)</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 600; color: #2f9e44; line-height: 1.15; margin-top: 4px;\">2.6%</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.82rem; color:#6c757d; margin-top: 2px;\">52ᵗʰ percentile</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px;&#10;       background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);&#10;       min-width: 170px; flex: 1;\">\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.80rem; color:#6c757d; letter-spacing: .02em; text-transform: uppercase;\">Fed Funds target</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1d3557; line-height: 1.15; margin-top: 4px;\">3.25%</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.82rem; color:#6c757d; margin-top: 2px;\">Upper bound, period avg</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px;&#10;       background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);&#10;       min-width: 170px; flex: 1;\">\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.80rem; color:#6c757d; letter-spacing: .02em; text-transform: uppercase;\">10Y Treasury</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1d3557; line-height: 1.15; margin-top: 4px;\">4.00%</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.82rem; color:#6c757d; margin-top: 2px;\">Period avg</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px;&#10;       background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);&#10;       min-width: 170px; flex: 1;\">\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.80rem; color:#6c757d; letter-spacing: .02em; text-transform: uppercase;\">S&amp;P 500 (YTD)</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 600; color: #2f9e44; line-height: 1.15; margin-top: 4px;\">+4.0%</div>\n<div style=